3 garnishment, or any other process whatsoever, nor shall any assignment thereof be
4 enforceable in any court. Except retirement benefits accrued or accruing to any
5 employee of a state postsecondary educational institution through a retirement
6 program sponsored by the state postsecondary educational institution on or after
7 January 1, 1998, shall be subject to the tax imposed by KRS 141.020, to the extent
8 provided in KRS 141.010 and 141.0215.
9 (3) Except as provided in KRS Chapter 44, the purchase of liability insurance for
10 members of governing boards, faculty and staff of institutions of higher education
11 in this state shall not be construed to be a waiver of sovereign immunity or any
12 other immunity or privilege.
